<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880916-0032 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Apple Computer Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AAPL </CO><IN> EDP </IN><TEXT>   Apple Computer Inc. plans to introduce a new low-priced version of its Apple II computer today, aimed at the home market and first-time computer buyers.    The machine, called the Apple IIc Plus, will sell for $675. The entire system, including a one color monitor, will sell for $859 and the system, with a full-color monitor, will sell for $1,099. The machine has color graphics capabilities.    Apple, Cupertino, Calif., said new model is three times faster, and less expensive than its predecessor, the Apple IIc. Its disk drives can store more than five times the capacity of disks used in earlier models, Apple said. </TEXT></DOC>